HEADWORD: Mesolite
<hw>Mes"o*lite</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Meso-</ets> + <ets>-lite</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A zeolitic mineral, grayish white or yellowish, occuring in
delicate groups of crystals, also fibrous massive. It is a hydrous
silicate of alumina, lime, and soda.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

